00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:04.390 align:middle line:90%
Pitocin.

00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> I asked to keep
upping the Pit.

00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:09.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Probably about 90% of our
patients at some point are

00:12:09.740 --> 00:12:11.600 align:middle line:90%
on some type of augmentation.

00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:13.250 align:middle line:84%
>> She's not anywhere
near adequacy,

00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:14.630 align:middle line:90%
so we would have to keep it up.

00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.000 align:middle line:84%
>> If you're not making that
change in that segment of time

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:18.500 align:middle line:84%
that we're looking for,
then we're going to try

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:19.790 align:middle line:90%
to facilitate things.

00:12:19.790 --> 00:12:20.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Maybe start Pit?

00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:22.700 align:middle line:90%
So we have the Pitocin.

00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:24.260 align:middle line:90%
Pit at 6:30.

00:12:24.260 --> 00:12:26.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Hospitals are businesses.

00:12:26.150 --> 00:12:29.150 align:middle line:10%
They want those beds
filled and emptied.

00:12:29.150 --> 00:12:31.670 align:middle line:10%
They don't want women hanging
around in the labor room.

00:12:31.670 --> 00:12:33.212 align:middle line:10%
You have this feeling
of the hospital

00:12:33.212 --> 00:12:36.050 align:middle line:10%
where there's a limit to how
