00:14:05.590 --> 00:14:06.970 align:middle line:90%
It will flow into your veins.

00:14:06.970 --> 00:14:11.050 align:middle line:84%
Pitocin makes contractions
longer and stronger and closer

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:15.650 align:middle line:84%
together, so then the pain
of labor is much worse.

00:14:15.650 --> 00:14:19.060 align:middle line:84%
So you go with that for a while
because you have the epidural,

00:14:19.060 --> 00:14:21.370 align:middle line:84%
but eventually the pain
of the contractions

00:14:21.370 --> 00:14:22.660 align:middle line:90%
is overwhelming the epidural.

00:14:22.660 --> 00:14:23.980 align:middle line:90%
You need to up the epidural.

00:14:23.980 --> 00:14:26.390 align:middle line:84%
And then labor slows down
more because of that,

00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:27.910 align:middle line:90%
so then you need more Pitocin.

00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:30.430 align:middle line:84%
Now you're not feeling the
pain of the extra Pitocin

00:14:30.430 --> 00:14:32.950 align:middle line:84%
because you've got the
epidural, but your baby

00:14:32.950 --> 00:14:36.790 align:middle line:84%
is getting compressed blood an
oxygen supply, because Pitocin

00:14:36.790 --> 00:14:39.580 align:middle line:84%
contractions last so
long and are so strong,

00:14:39.580 --> 00:14:42.950 align:middle line:84%
the blood and oxygen flow
to the baby is compromised.

00:14:42.950 --> 00:14:45.550 align:middle line:84%
So then the baby's likely
to go into distress.

00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:47.740 align:middle line:10%
And then you're sent off
for an emergency cesarean

00:14:47.740 --> 00:14:50.050 align:middle line:10%
from a baby in distress
from contractions

00:14:50.050 --> 00:14:51.820 align:middle line:10%
induced by the
Pitocin, which was

00:14:51.820 --> 00:14:53.440 align:middle line:10%
necessitated by the epidural.

00:14:53.440 --> 00:14:55.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Step by step, one
intervention leads to a series

00:14:55.910 --> 00:14:56.710 align:middle line:90%
of interventions.

00:14:56.710 --> 00:14:59.428 align:middle line:84%
And the net result is the mother
finally ends up with a cesarean

00:14:59.428 --> 00:15:00.970 align:middle line:84%
and everybody says,
thank God we were

00:15:00.970 --> 00:15:02.560 align:middle line:84%
able to do all those
interventions to save

00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:03.360 align:middle line:90%
your baby.

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:04.810 align:middle line:84%
The fact of the
matter is if they

00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:07.390 align:middle line:84%
didn't stop the cascade of
interventions, none of that

00:15:07.390 --> 00:15:08.570 align:middle line:90%
would have been necessary.

00:15:08.570 --> 00:15:11.110 align:middle line:10%
>> There is clearly an
association with induction

00:15:11.110 --> 00:15:13.060 align:middle line:10%
of labor and cesarean delivery.

00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:15.130 align:middle line:84%
>> People don't have
the information.

00:15:15.130 --> 00:15:18.380 align:middle line:84%
When you look at
obstetrics in general,

00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:22.690 align:middle line:84%
there's been a series of
very intense interventions

00:15:22.690 --> 00:15:24.700 align:middle line:84%
that physicians have
been doing day in

00:15:24.700 --> 00:15:26.860 align:middle line:84%
and day out to
millions of women.

00:15:26.860 --> 00:15:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And there's not a
medically justified reason

00:15:29.200 --> 00:15:30.430 align:middle line:90%
for doing those things.

00:15:30.430 --> 00:15:33.760 align:middle line:84%
Even common sense-- I mean
the idea of lying down

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:37.960 align:middle line:84%
with your legs up being the most
comfortable or logical position

00:15:37.960 --> 00:15:40.651 align:middle line:90%
to give birth.

00:15:40.651 --> 00:15:43.810 align:middle line:84%
>> The more you can move through
your labor and the more you can

00:15:43.810 --> 00:15:46.720 align:middle line:84%
move through contractions,
they don't seem as intense.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:49.540 align:middle line:10%
To lay still-- it's like,
who would want to do this?

00:15:49.540 --> 00:15:54.760 align:middle line:10%
I just want to get out of
this bed and move my hips.

00:15:54.760 --> 00:15:57.610 align:middle line:84%
>> The lithotomy position
is the most physiologically

00:15:57.610 --> 00:16:00.430 align:middle line:84%
dysfunctional position
