00:17:54.320 --> 00:17:56.570 align:middle line:10%
an absolute dire emergency.

00:17:56.570 --> 00:18:00.170 align:middle line:10%
So why should women feel
confident about giving birth

00:18:00.170 --> 00:18:03.270 align:middle line:10%
when the whole culture is
telling them this is scary,

00:18:03.270 --> 00:18:04.340 align:middle line:10%
this is dangerous?

00:18:04.340 --> 00:18:06.603 align:middle line:10%
>> Women expect to have
traumatic experiences.

00:18:06.603 --> 00:18:08.270 align:middle line:10%
That's why they're
all having epidurals,

00:18:08.270 --> 00:18:10.910 align:middle line:10%
because they're terrified
of what this is.

00:18:10.910 --> 00:18:13.710 align:middle line:84%
>> The births on television
are very dramatic.

00:18:13.710 --> 00:18:15.560 align:middle line:84%
I would be extremely
frightened, too,

00:18:15.560 --> 00:18:17.840 align:middle line:84%
if I saw these
women strapped in.

00:18:17.840 --> 00:18:20.030 align:middle line:10%
There is always
some sort of danger,

00:18:20.030 --> 00:18:22.490 align:middle line:10%
that the doctor comes
in and saves the women.

00:18:22.490 --> 00:18:25.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Mommy, the baby's heart rate
is going a little bit down.

00:18:25.220 --> 00:18:26.263 align:middle line:90%
And I don't like that.

