type and isolate it.

00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:52.450 align:middle line:90%


00:19:52.450 --> 00:19:55.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I'm totally
curious about your project.

00:19:55.610 --> 00:19:58.250 align:middle line:10%
I'm sorry I don't know more
about your work and who you are

00:19:58.250 --> 00:20:00.250 align:middle line:10%
and how long you've been
working on this project

00:20:00.250 --> 00:20:02.330 align:middle line:10%
and what got you interested
or fascinated and all

00:20:02.330 --> 00:20:03.820 align:middle line:10%
of that stuff, Abby, for sure.

00:20:03.820 --> 00:20:04.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:06.670 align:middle line:90%
I mean, Ricki is the one who--

00:20:06.670 --> 00:20:10.540 align:middle line:84%
Ricki had two births,
the second one at home.

00:20:10.540 --> 00:20:13.360 align:middle line:10%
So she brought me into
this just as a filmmaker.

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:15.670 align:middle line:10%
And then I just happened
to get pregnant.

00:20:15.670 --> 00:20:17.515 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh my God.

00:20:17.515 --> 00:20:18.520 align:middle line:90%
Are you pregnant now?

00:20:18.520 --> 00:20:19.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:19.720 --> 00:20:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, congratulations.

00:20:20.890 --> 00:20:21.700 align:middle line:90%
That's awesome.

00:20:21.700 --> 00:20:23.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:23.960 align:middle line:90%
One of the reasons.

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:27.190 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to do this project
is I wanted to explore--

00:20:27.190 --> 00:20:31.330 align:middle line:84%
for me, having the two very
different birth experiences.

00:20:31.330 --> 00:20:34.880 align:middle line:84%
Both really amazing
and beautiful.

00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:39.100 align:middle line:84%
But for me, it was
just as much a priority

00:20:39.100 --> 00:20:42.190 align:middle line:84%
to have the memory of
the process of being

00:20:42.190 --> 00:20:45.280 align:middle line:84%
pregnant and delivering and the
rite of passage and remembering

00:20:45.280 --> 00:20:46.910 align:middle line:90%
everything, feeling everything.

00:20:46.910 --> 00:20:51.785 align:middle line:84%
And so many of my peers
and women in our society,

00:20:51.785 --> 00:20:52.910 align:middle line:90%
they don't care about that.

00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:55.270 align:middle line:84%
They just want the end result of
the healthy baby in their arms.

00:20:55.270 --> 00:20:56.890 align:middle line:84%
And they don't care
how it got there.

00:20:56.890 --> 00:20:59.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's something I
really wanted to explore,

00:20:59.530 --> 00:21:01.750 align:middle line:84%
because I feel like so
many women are missing

00:21:01.750 --> 00:21:03.550 align:middle line:90%
this amazing opportunity.

00:21:03.550 --> 00:21:08.020 align:middle line:84%
And this life-altering
experience.

00:21:08.020 --> 00:21:10.600 align:middle line:84%
I feel like so much of
who I am today comes

00:21:10.600 --> 00:21:12.340 align:middle line:90%
from that experience.

00:21:12.340 --> 00:21:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I know.

00:21:14.180 --> 00:21:15.920 align:middle line:90%
It's hugely transformative.

00:21:15.920 --> 00:21:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And I think just
looking at-- you're

00:21:17.950 --> 00:21:20.410 align:middle line:84%
going to be transformed by
your birth, like it or not.

00:21:20.410 --> 00:21:21.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:21:21.430 --> 00:21:31.990 align:middle line:90%


00:21:31.990 --> 00:21:34.390 align:middle line:84%
>> A woman, as
long as she lives,

00:21:34.390 --> 00:21:40.230 align:middle line:84%
will remember how she was
made to feel at her birth.

00:21:40.230 --> 00:21:42.270 align:middle line:84%
>> The way I've explained
birth sometimes,

00:21:42.270 --> 00:21:44.040 align:middle line:84%
at least my personal
experience to people,

00:21:44.040 --> 00:21:48.030 align:middle line:84%
is it's like you switch on
a light switch and you go

00:21:48.030 --> 00:21:49.950 align:middle line:90%
to the moon.

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:51.990 align:middle line:90%
It's an otherworldly experience.

00:21:51.990 --> 00:21:54.330 align:middle line:84%
Nothing compares
to the privilege

00:21:54.330 --> 00:21:57.930 align:middle line:84%
of giving life and the
responsibility of that.

00:21:57.930 --> 00:21:59.100 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:21:59.100 --> 00:22:01.500 align:middle line:84%
So if you don't
have the reverence

00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:03.780 align:middle line:84%
and the respect for that,
where do you go from there?

00:22:03.780 --> 00:22:10.270 align:middle line:90%


00:22:10.270 --> 00:22:13.150 align:middle line:84%
>> A woman really doesn't
need to be rescued.

00:22:13.150 --> 00:22:15.520 align:middle line:84%
It's not the place for the
knight in shining armor.

00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:18.880 align:middle line:10%
It's the place for her to
face her darkest moment

00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:21.190 align:middle line:10%
and lay claim to her
victory so that she

00:22:21.190 --> 00:22:23.770 align:middle line:10%
can lay claim to her victory
after she's done it, I think.

00:22:23.770 --> 00:22:28.940 align:middle line:90%


00:22:28.940 --> 00:22:32.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Many people have described
birth as a rite of passage.

00:22:32.060 --> 00:22:35.270 align:middle line:84%
And it is certainly a
life-altering experience.

00:22:35.270 --> 00:22:39.960 align:middle line:84%
And it can be a
beautiful, incredible,

00:22:39.960 --> 00:22:44.480 align:middle line:84%
empowering life-altering
experience or it can be

00:22:44.480 --> 00:22:50.580 align:middle line:84%
a devastating,
traumatic, scarring--

00:22:50.580 --> 00:22:53.650 align:middle line:84%
literally and
figuratively-- experience.

00:22:53.650 --> 00:22:55.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, we can take that.

00:22:55.080 --> 00:22:57.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Stand behind me.

00:22:57.510 --> 00:23:00.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Melba.

00:23:00.630 --> 00:23:02.400 align:middle line:90%
Melba, remember, no crying.

00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:03.900 align:middle line:90%
You got to breathe, OK?

00:23:03.900 --> 00:23:05.610 align:middle line:84%
>> We're going to put
you on a stretcher.

00:23:05.610 --> 00:23:06.960 align:middle line:84%
and then we're going
to take you to the OR.

00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:07.841 align:middle line:90%
>> It's time, OK?

00:23:07.841 --> 00:23:29.460 align:middle line:90%


00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:30.755 align:middle line:10%
>> We are completely lost.

00:23:30.755 --> 00:23:33.460 align:middle line:10%


00:23:33.460 --> 00:23:35.800 align:middle line:10%
And we have even
forgotten to raise

00:23:35.800 --> 00:23:40.330 align:middle line:10%
the most simple questions.

00:23:40.330 --> 00:23:42.604 align:middle line:10%
What are the basic
needs of women in labor?

00:23:42.604 --> 00:23:45.082 align:middle line:10%


00:23:45.082 --> 00:23:47.040 align:middle line:10%
And the fact that the
midwives have disappeared

00:23:47.040 --> 00:23:51.030 align:middle line:10%
is a symptom of lack
of understanding

00:23:51.030 --> 00:23:53.860 align:middle line:10%
of the basic needs
of women in labor.

00:23:53.860 --> 00:23:59.650 align:middle line:84%
Like a traveler who
suddenly can realize that

00:23:59.650 --> 00:24:02.260 align:middle line:90%
he took a wrong way.

00:24:02.260 --> 00:24:03.640 align:middle line:10%
He took a wrong way.

00:24:03.640 --> 00:24:06.070 align:middle line:10%
The best thing to
do in this case

00:24:06.070 --> 00:24:10.250 align:middle line:10%
is to go back to square
one, the point of departure,

00:24:10.250 --> 00:24:12.140 align:middle line:10%
and to take another direction.

00:24:12.140 --> 00:24:24.042 align:middle line:90%


00:24:24.042 --> 00:24:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, that's what I
should do-- take Flatbush.

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:29.920 align:middle line:90%


00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:33.370 align:middle line:84%
I went to nursing school
at Columbia University

00:24:33.370 --> 00:24:36.610 align:middle line:84%
and then became an obstetrical
nurse in the labor room, where

00:24:36.610 --> 00:24:38.470 align:middle line:90%
I practiced for five years.

00:24:38.470 --> 00:24:40.750 align:middle line:84%
After that, I went
to midwifery school

00:24:40.750 --> 00:24:43.780 align:middle line:84%
and then practiced for a
year in hospital, four years

00:24:43.780 --> 00:24:45.730 align:middle line:84%
at an out-of-hospital
birthing center,

00:24:45.730 --> 00:24:48.910 align:middle line:84%
and then I began my
own solo home birth

00:24:48.910 --> 00:24:51.820 align:middle line:84%
practice, which I've been
doing for the last 10 years.

00:24:51.820 --> 00:24:54.220 align:middle line:84%
I like to see them
in their homes.

00:24:54.220 --> 00:24:56.270 align:middle line:84%
The rationale for
that is, first of all,

00:24:56.270 --> 00:24:58.062 align:middle line:84%
they're going to have
the baby in the home.

00:24:58.062 --> 00:25:03.640 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, I'd rather be on their
turf than them be on my turf.

00:25:03.640 --> 00:25:07.720 align:middle line:10%
I'd rather them build
a comfortable ambience

00:25:07.720 --> 00:25:10.250 align:middle line:10%
that I get to see them
in on a regular basis,

00:25:10.250 --> 00:25:12.370 align:middle line:10%
so that by the time
it's time for the birth,

00:25:12.370 --> 00:25:16.120 align:middle line:10%
they know where their
rooms are, their bathrooms.

00:25:16.120 --> 00:25:19.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's pretty much just the
philosophical underpinnings

00:25:19.540 --> 00:25:23.365 align:middle line:84%
of giving the power
back to the woman.

00:25:23.365 --> 00:25:27.632 align:middle line:90%


00:25:27.632 --> 00:25:29.090 align:middle line:84%
Breathe in deep
through your mouth.

00:25:29.090 --> 00:25:31.740 align:middle line:90%


00:25:31.740 --> 00:25:33.660 align:middle line:90%
They sound really clear.

00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:34.650 align:middle line:90%
That's really good.

00:25:34.650 --> 00:25:35.880 align:middle line:90%
One colander is good.

00:25:35.880 --> 00:25:37.860 align:middle line:84%
I can use that to put
my instruments in,

00:25:37.860 --> 00:25:39.280 align:middle line:90%
the glove and blah, blah, blah.

00:25:39.280 --> 00:25:42.190 align:middle line:84%
>> And then the placenta,
I have a large freezer bag.

00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:42.990 align:middle line:90%
Is that OK?

00:25:42.990 --> 00:25:43.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:25:43.790 --> 00:25:45.810 align:middle line:84%
Actually, do two
gallon-size Ziploc bags.

00:25:45.810 --> 00:25:47.550 align:middle line:84%
It's better for New
York City freezers,

00:25:47.550 --> 00:25:49.600 align:middle line:84%
because you can put
some masking tape on it.

00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:50.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Placenta.

00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:51.000 align:middle line:90%
>> You can do it.

00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:51.780 align:middle line:90%
You want to go first?

00:25:51.780 --> 00:25:54.197 align:middle line:84%
Or you want me to show you
first and then you take a turn?

00:25:54.197 --> 00:25:55.290 align:middle line:90%
>> You go first.

00:25:55.290 --> 00:25:56.250 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:25:56.250 --> 00:25:58.110 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you
think, pretty big?

00:25:58.110 --> 00:26:00.160 align:middle line:84%
You think it's
ready to come out?

00:26:00.160 --> 00:26:00.960 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so.

00:26:00.960 --> 00:26:01.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Definitely.

00:26:01.770 --> 00:26:02.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:26:02.570 --> 00:26:05.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I do believe that women
who choose home birth,

00:26:05.640 --> 00:26:07.410 align:middle line:90%
they do share something.

00:26:07.410 --> 00:26:10.170 align:middle line:84%
It could be just a
feeling that she knows

00:26:10.170 --> 00:26:11.730 align:middle line:90%
how she wants to do things.

00:26:11.730 --> 00:26:13.560 align:middle line:84%
And then I think
when she's in labor,

00:26:13.560 --> 00:26:17.130 align:middle line:84%
she can interact with her
labor in a different way

00:26:17.130 --> 00:26:19.530 align:middle line:84%
than if everybody is
doing things to her

00:26:19.530 --> 00:26:22.700 align:middle line:90%
and making decisions about her.

00:26:22.700 --> 00:26:23.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Baby.

00:26:23.650 --> 00:26:28.590 align:middle line:90%


00:26:28.590 --> 00:26:29.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I checked.

00:26:29.460 --> 00:26:30.630 align:middle line:90%
It is warm.

00:26:30.630 --> 00:26:32.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:26:32.050 --> 00:26:32.850 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:26:32.850 --> 00:26:34.270 align:middle line:90%
>> That's really close, Lauren.

00:26:34.270 --> 00:26:35.070 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:26:35.070 --> 00:26:39.090 align:middle line:90%


00:26:39.090 --> 00:26:45.090 align:middle line:10%
>> Today, what we have to
discover is how easy birth can

00:26:45.090 --> 00:26:50.220 align:middle line:10%
be when we don't try to
make things too complicated,

00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:55.410 align:middle line:10%
when ideally there is nobody
around but an experienced,

00:26:55.410 --> 00:26:59.490 align:middle line:10%
motherly, and silent,
low profile midwife.

00:26:59.490 --> 00:27:03.980 align:middle line:90%


00:27:03.980 --> 00:27:05.130 align:middle line:90%
>> No, no.

00:27:05.130 --> 00:27:07.894 align:middle line:90%
>> Mama?

00:27:07.894 --> 00:27:09.295 align:middle line:90%
>> There she is.

00:27:09.295 --> 00:27:15.210 align:middle line:90%


00:27:15.210 --> 00:27:19.392 align:middle line:84%
>> Somebody else look at the
time, because I missed it.

00:27:19.392 --> 00:27:20.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Make sure she's
above the water.

00:27:20.850 --> 00:27:23.160 align:middle line:90%
Let me just see.

00:27:23.160 --> 00:27:24.600 align:middle line:90%
OK, good.

00:27:24.600 --> 00:27:26.010 align:middle line:90%
I got it.

00:27:26.010 --> 00:27:27.720 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:29.880 align:middle line:90%
You're done.

00:27:29.880 --> 00:27:31.730 align:middle line:90%
She's fine.

00:27:31.730 --> 00:27:32.530 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:27:32.530 --> 00:27:33.655 align:middle line:90%
Do whatever you need to do.

00:27:33.655 --> 00:27:35.211 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to
keep an eye on her.

00:27:35.211 --> 00:27:40.370 align:middle line:90%


00:27:40.370 --> 00:27:42.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:27:42.320 --> 00:27:43.508 align:middle line:90%
Be careful.

00:27:43.508 --> 00:27:44.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Cord's a little short.

00:27:44.550 --> 00:27:45.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, a little short.

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:46.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:27:46.260 --> 00:27:52.010 align:middle line:90%


00:27:52.010 --> 00:27:56.510 align:middle line:84%
>> I went online and I found
that New York hospitals had

00:27:56.510 --> 00:27:59.360 align:middle line:84%
some of the highest cesarean
rates in the nation.

00:27:59.360 --> 00:28:00.920 align:middle line:84%
That actually
really surprised me.

00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I guess I expected New York
women to be more like, hey,

00:28:03.950 --> 00:28:05.330 align:middle line:90%
I'm taking charge.

00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:06.770 align:middle line:90%
So I was surprised.

00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:08.100 align:middle line:90%
And I was scared.

00:28:08.100 --> 00:28:10.640 align:middle line:84%
I knew what interventions
I was OK with.

00:28:10.640 --> 00:28:12.740 align:middle line:90%
And they were pretty much zero.

00:28:12.740 --> 00:28:14.420 align:middle line:84%
I really understand
that things can

00:28:14.420 --> 00:28:16.940 align:middle line:84%
go wrong during pregnancy,
just like with anything else.

00:28:16.940 --> 00:28:20.810 align:middle line:84%
But I don't want that to be
precipitated, so to speak.

00:28:20.810 --> 00:28:24.360 align:middle line:84%
I said, David, this
isn't looking good.

00:28:24.360 --> 00:28:27.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I started to
interview midwives in the city.

00:28:27.810 --> 00:28:30.370 align:middle line:10%
I just feel like
I trust my body.

00:28:30.370 --> 00:28:31.170 align:middle line:10%
>> That's great.

00:28:31.170 --> 00:28:33.780 align:middle line:10%
>> I really just want to--

00:28:33.780 --> 00:28:36.710 align:middle line:10%
I have a feeling that this is
the way you run things anyway.

00:28:36.710 --> 00:28:41.000 align:middle line:84%
But I just wanted to let my
body do what it's going to do.

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:43.410 align:middle line:90%
>> And it so does.

00:28:43.410 --> 00:28:44.540 align:middle line:90%
I don't even run things.

00:28:44.540 --> 00:28:45.890 align:middle line:90%
Your body runs things.

00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:47.870 align:middle line:90%
And it's respecting that.

00:28:47.870 --> 00:28:50.900 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm like the
guardian of safety

00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:53.010 align:middle line:90%
and the witness of your process.

00:28:53.010 --> 00:28:55.730 align:middle line:84%
I really do firmly
believe, oftentimes,

00:28:55.730 --> 00:28:57.990 align:middle line:84%
that the body is
smarter than me.

00:28:57.990 --> 00:28:59.300 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not that dumb.

00:28:59.300 --> 00:29:02.360 align:middle line:90%


00:29:02.360 --> 00:29:03.770 align:middle line:90%
>> I spoke to her yesterday.

00:29:03.770 --> 00:29:05.270 align:middle line:84%
She did not attend
this appointment.

00:29:05.270 --> 00:29:05.480 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:06.980 align:middle line:84%
But you were able
to reach her here.

00:29:06.980 --> 00:29:07.970 align:middle line:90%
OK, I'll call her.

00:29:07.970 --> 00:29:09.260 align:middle line:90%
Remember, that tongue ring?

00:29:09.260 --> 00:29:10.280 align:middle line:90%
Let me see.

00:29:10.280 --> 00:29:12.440 align:middle line:84%
That's got to come
out before delivery.

00:29:12.440 --> 00:29:15.990 align:middle line:84%
You didn't push that long
to have this 9-pound baby.

00:29:15.990 --> 00:29:17.310 align:middle line:90%
You did a fabulous job.

00:29:17.310 --> 00:29:18.110 align:middle line:90%
I was so impressed.

00:29:18.110 --> 00:29:19.652 align:middle line:10%
A lot of women walk
in with the ideas

00:29:19.652 --> 00:29:21.183 align:middle line:10%
that I definitely
want an epidural

00:29:21.183 --> 00:29:22.850 align:middle line:10%
or I don't want
anything-- or maybe just

00:29:22.850 --> 00:29:23.990 align:middle line:10%
a little bit of sedation.

00:29:23.990 --> 00:29:25.250 align:middle line:90%
And it's OK.

00:29:25.250 --> 00:29:26.180 align:middle line:90%
She has options.

00:29:26.180 --> 00:29:28.640 align:middle line:84%
I know you want to go natural
and do everything normal,

00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:29.520 align:middle line:90%
and that's fine.

00:29:29.520 --> 00:29:32.000 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take
one step at a time.

00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:34.468 align:middle line:84%
That's all we can do--
one contraction at a time.

00:29:34.468 --> 00:29:36.260 align:middle line:84%
Next thing you know,
this baby will be out.

00:29:36.260 --> 00:29:39.450 align:middle line:84%
You'll be breastfeeding
and laughing up a storm.

00:29:39.450 --> 00:29:40.250 align:middle line:90%
>> I hope.

00:29:40.250 --> 00:29:40.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:29:40.580 --> 00:29:42.330 align:middle line:84%
They all come out,
one way or the other.

00:29:42.330 --> 00:29:43.730 align:middle line:84%
I have three
beautiful daughters.

00:29:43.730 --> 00:29:45.980 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, I wasn't
able to have a midwife.

00:29:45.980 --> 00:29:46.920 align:middle line:90%
I was high-risk.

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:49.940 align:middle line:84%
So I had an M.D. and he
wasn't with me the whole time.

00:29:49.940 --> 00:29:52.650 align:middle line:84%
He came in to do the
delivery and he would leave.

00:29:52.650 --> 00:29:56.792 align:middle line:84%
And I knew then that there's
got to be a different way.

00:29:56.792 --> 00:29:59.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you were saying
you've never missed a birth.

00:29:59.000 --> 00:30:00.208 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I don't miss births.

00:30:00.208 --> 00:30:01.850 align:middle line:90%
I missed one on 9/11.

00:30:01.850 --> 00:30:04.440 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't get back
into the city at all.

00:30:04.440 --> 00:30:05.240 align:middle line:90%
>> That's it.

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:06.110 align:middle line:90%
That's the only one you missed?

00:30:06.110 --> 00:30:06.830 align:middle line:90%
>> That's the only one I missed.

00:30:06.830 --> 00:30:09.140 align:middle line:84%
The baby's head is
coming down now, Gayle.

00:30:09.140 --> 00:30:11.120 align:middle line:10%
And eventually, that
pressure will just stay.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:12.870 align:middle line:10%
But I'd like to know
about that before you

00:30:12.870 --> 00:30:14.145 align:middle line:10%
do your little squat thing.

00:30:14.145 --> 00:30:15.770 align:middle line:10%
Women come to me all
the time that have

00:30:15.770 --> 00:30:18.800 align:middle line:10%
had births in a
traditional OB/GYN setting.

00:30:18.800 --> 00:30:20.990 align:middle line:84%
And it is a totally
different experience.

00:30:20.990 --> 00:30:22.080 align:middle line:90%
And they spread the word.

00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:25.310 align:middle line:84%
But unfortunately, it's just
not enough to turn this around

00:30:25.310 --> 00:30:26.190 align:middle line:90%
for us.

00:30:26.190 --> 00:30:27.140 align:middle line:90%
>> You want to go in?

00:30:27.140 --> 00:30:27.940 align:middle line:90%
>> You go in.

00:30:27.940 --> 00:30:31.570 align:middle line:90%


00:30:31.570 --> 00:30:36.840 align:middle line:84%
>> We're going to
28th and 8th, please.

00:30:36.840 --> 00:30:37.990 align:middle line:90%
Can I tell you something?

00:30:37.990 --> 00:30:41.200 align:middle line:84%
It is so hard to find
this birth stuff.

00:30:41.200 --> 00:30:42.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:43.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh my God.

00:30:43.170 --> 00:30:45.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Is the researcher
still doing stuff or no?

00:30:45.060 --> 00:30:46.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:30:46.650 --> 00:30:50.550 align:middle line:84%
>> That was the
twilight sleep cribs.

00:30:50.550 --> 00:30:53.100 align:middle line:90%
It looks like a torture chamber.

00:30:53.100 --> 00:30:55.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Look at what
they did to them.

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:56.750 align:middle line:90%
It was a straitjacket.

00:30:56.750 --> 00:30:58.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh my God.

00:30:58.110 --> 00:30:59.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Look at that.

00:30:59.280 --> 00:31:01.140 align:middle line:90%
They blindfolded them.

00:31:01.140 --> 00:31:02.490 align:middle line:90%
>> What year is this?

00:31:02.490 --> 00:31:03.465 align:middle line:90%
>> This is in the 20s.

00:31:03.465 --> 00:31:10.410 align:middle line:90%


00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The drug scopolamine
was invented in Germany

00:31:13.170 --> 00:31:14.550 align:middle line:90%
in the early 1900s.

00:31:14.550 --> 00:31:18.760 align:middle line:84%
And American women
found out about it.

00:31:18.760 --> 00:31:20.520 align:middle line:84%
Remember that at
that time, women

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:23.820 align:middle line:84%
were still being told that
the pain of childbirth

00:31:23.820 --> 00:31:25.320 align:middle line:90%
was the curse of Eve.

00:31:25.320 --> 00:31:28.230 align:middle line:84%
And that it was because of
Eve's sin in the Garden of Eden

00:31:28.230 --> 00:31:30.430 align:middle line:84%
that women had to suffer
during childbirth.

00:31:30.430 --> 00:31:33.270 align:middle line:84%
So you can imagine how the
modern liberated feminist

00:31:33.270 --> 00:31:35.250 align:middle line:84%
attitude at the time
would be, I certainly

00:31:35.250 --> 00:31:36.540 align:middle line:90%
do not have to suffer.

00:31:36.540 --> 00:31:38.460 align:middle line:10%
And if there are drugs
around that keep me

00:31:38.460 --> 00:31:40.002 align:middle line:10%
from having to
suffer, then I'm going

00:31:40.002 --> 00:31:43.710 align:middle line:10%
to go find those drugs,
because I'm a modern woman.

00:31:43.710 --> 00:31:46.440 align:middle line:84%
Women thought that it took
away pain during childbirth,

00:31:46.440 --> 00:31:47.280 align:middle line:90%
but it doesn't.

00:31:47.280 --> 00:31:50.590 align:middle line:84%
It actually just takes away
your memory of the experience.

00:31:50.590 --> 00:31:54.270 align:middle line:84%
So scopolamine spread rapidly
across the United States.

00:31:54.270 --> 00:31:57.150 align:middle line:84%
And by the 1960s,
almost everyone

00:31:57.150 --> 00:31:58.590 align:middle line:90%
was having twilight sleep.

00:31:58.590 --> 00:32:00.720 align:middle line:84%
Now, it does take away
memory, but it also

00:32:00.720 --> 00:32:03.660 align:middle line:90%
takes away self-control.

00:32:03.660 --> 00:32:05.370 align:middle line:90%
It takes away self-awareness.

00:32:05.370 --> 00:32:08.910 align:middle line:84%
So women screamed and
tried to climb the walls

00:32:08.910 --> 00:32:11.130 align:middle line:84%
and spit in people's
faces and tried

00:32:11.130 --> 00:32:13.110 align:middle line:84%
to claw the face of the
doctor or the nurse.

00:32:13.110 --> 00:32:16.200 align:middle line:84%
So the hospitals developed the
technique of strapping women

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.210 align:middle line:84%
to the hospital
bed with lambswool,

00:32:18.210 --> 00:32:19.690 align:middle line:84%
because if you
used anything else,

00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:20.910 align:middle line:84%
it would leave marks
on their wrists

00:32:20.910 --> 00:32:21.990 align:middle line:84%
and then their
husbands would want

00:32:21.990 --> 00:32:23.320 align:middle line:90%
to know what was done to them.

00:32:23.320 --> 00:32:25.440 align:middle line:84%
And so women were
literally strapped to beds

00:32:25.440 --> 00:32:27.990 align:middle line:84%
and left there for
days, sometimes

00:32:27.990 --> 00:32:29.580 align:middle line:90%
in their own poop and pee.

00:32:29.580 --> 00:32:32.565 align:middle line:84%
It was a very brutal period
in American birthing history.

00:32:32.565 --> 00:32:36.180 align:middle line:90%


00:32:36.180 --> 00:32:39.330 align:middle line:84%
>> If you look at obstetrics
for the last 50 years,

00:32:39.330 --> 00:32:40.410 align:middle line:90%
what do you find?

00:32:40.410 --> 00:32:44.070 align:middle line:84%
In the 1930s, they were giving
X-rays on every pregnant woman

00:32:44.070 --> 00:32:45.630 align:middle line:90%
to measure her pelvis.

00:32:45.630 --> 00:32:48.030 align:middle line:84%
And then in the
1940s, they discovered

00:32:48.030 --> 00:32:50.770 align:middle line:84%
that that caused the
baby to have cancer,

00:32:50.770 --> 00:32:52.320 align:middle line:90%
so they had to stop it.

00:32:52.320 --> 00:32:55.410 align:middle line:84%
And then in the
1950s and 60s, they

00:32:55.410 --> 00:32:57.970 align:middle line:84%
had another drug
called thalidomide,

00:32:57.970 --> 00:33:01.350 align:middle line:84%
which caused babies to be
born without arms and legs.

00:33:01.350 --> 00:33:03.270 align:middle line:90%
And then they had to stop that.

00:33:03.270 --> 00:33:06.700 align:middle line:84%
But you see, in every case,
it was after the fact.

00:33:06.700 --> 00:33:10.710 align:middle line:84%
In the 1990s, they
were giving Cytotec

00:33:10.710 --> 00:33:15.540 align:middle line:84%
to induce labor in women who
had had a previous cesarean.

00:33:15.540 --> 00:33:18.990 align:middle line:10%
And they ended up with
hundreds and hundreds

00:33:18.990 --> 00:33:24.540 align:middle line:10%
of ruptured uteruses and
many, many, many dead babies

00:33:24.540 --> 00:33:28.590 align:middle line:10%
before they found
out, finally, in 1999

00:33:28.590 --> 00:33:30.060 align:middle line:10%
that they shouldn't do that.

00:33:30.060 --> 00:33:33.270 align:middle line:84%
But you see, there's
not a good history

00:33:33.270 --> 00:33:39.510 align:middle line:84%
in obstetric practice of careful
study of the long-term effects

00:33:39.510 --> 00:33:41.940 align:middle line:90%
of all these interventions.

00:33:41.940 --> 00:33:47.820 align:middle line:84%
This is why if you really
want a humanized birth,

00:33:47.820 --> 00:33:52.140 align:middle line:84%
the best thing to do is to get
the hell out of the hospital.

00:33:52.140 --> 00:34:13.650 align:middle line:90%


00:34:13.650 --> 00:34:18.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Historically, the birth
movement grew apace again after

00:34:18.150 --> 00:34:20.790 align:middle line:84%
it was basically cut out from
under the midwives at the turn

00:34:20.790 --> 00:34:24.330 align:middle line:84%
