00:48:29.570 --> 00:48:30.575 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah?

00:48:30.575 --> 00:48:31.700 align:middle line:90%
Because that's how we feel.

00:48:31.700 --> 00:48:35.270 align:middle line:84%
If we changed our lines
at the last minute--

00:48:35.270 --> 00:48:37.050 align:middle line:84%
>> You can't change
too-too late.

00:48:37.050 --> 00:48:38.300 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I don't mean like that.

00:48:38.300 --> 00:48:41.265 align:middle line:84%
But I mean suddenly if I was
still breech at full term

00:48:41.265 --> 00:48:42.065 align:middle line:90%
or something.

00:48:42.065 --> 00:48:43.107 align:middle line:90%
>> That's not a big deal.

00:48:43.107 --> 00:48:45.030 align:middle line:84%
We'll know that anyhow,
one way or another.

00:48:45.030 --> 00:48:46.580 align:middle line:84%
I don't think we're going
to have those surprises.

00:48:46.580 --> 00:48:47.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:48:47.380 --> 00:48:49.910 align:middle line:84%
>> I've had Moritz
back me many times.

00:48:49.910 --> 00:48:54.110 align:middle line:90%
And I could go to St Vincent's.

00:48:54.110 --> 00:48:55.250 align:middle line:90%
We could go to Moritz.

00:48:55.250 --> 00:48:58.580 align:middle line:84%
It would depend on what
the circumstances were.

00:48:58.580 --> 00:49:00.930 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, it was just
like I was thinking, well,

00:49:00.930 --> 00:49:04.130 align:middle line:84%
if we do a home birth
and we transfer,

00:49:04.130 --> 00:49:06.710 align:middle line:84%
I love the idea of possibly
being able to transfer

00:49:06.710 --> 00:49:07.880 align:middle line:90%
to a birth center.

00:49:07.880 --> 00:49:09.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:49:09.050 --> 00:49:10.050 align:middle line:90%
>> You know what I mean?

00:49:10.050 --> 00:49:11.180 align:middle line:90%
And you would be able--

00:49:11.180 --> 00:49:15.540 align:middle line:84%
>> But if you transfer, you're
not going to a birth center

00:49:15.540 --> 00:49:16.353 align:middle line:90%
for the most part.

00:49:16.353 --> 00:49:17.520 align:middle line:90%
You have to think like that.

00:49:17.520 --> 00:49:22.630 align:middle line:84%
If you transfer, it's because
you need intervention.

00:49:22.630 --> 00:49:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:49:23.430 --> 00:49:26.010 align:middle line:84%
My only fear, which
is not even a fear,

00:49:26.010 --> 00:49:29.700 align:middle line:84%
is that I would suddenly in the
heat of labor change my mind

00:49:29.700 --> 00:49:33.240 align:middle line:90%
and say, Oh my God.

00:49:33.240 --> 00:49:34.270 align:middle line:90%
I think I'm dying.

00:49:34.270 --> 00:49:35.820 align:middle line:90%
I need to be in a hospital.

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:38.670 align:middle line:84%
>> You're meeting the midwife
who's going to write the book,

00:49:38.670 --> 00:49:40.380 align:middle line:84%
Home Birth Midwife
Begged for Cesarean.

00:49:40.380 --> 00:49:40.650 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:49:40.650 --> 00:49:41.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Because I did.

00:49:41.340 --> 00:49:42.140 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:49:42.140 --> 00:49:47.460 align:middle line:90%


00:49:47.460 --> 00:49:52.050 align:middle line:84%
>> As much as I've had training
in midwifery and as much

00:49:52.050 --> 00:49:55.380 align:middle line:84%
as I've been caring for women
in labor for the last 25 years

00:49:55.380 --> 00:49:58.650 align:middle line:84%
of my life, I would have to
say that I was not your model

00:49:58.650 --> 00:49:59.585 align:middle line:90%
patient.

00:49:59.585 --> 00:50:00.960 align:middle line:84%
The only good
thing I have to say

00:50:00.960 --> 00:50:02.880 align:middle line:84%
is that I get to
labor in the day.

00:50:02.880 --> 00:50:05.790 align:middle line:84%
I would have walked
myself over to Beth.

00:50:05.790 --> 00:50:09.340 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I'm surprised
that I didn't.

00:50:09.340 --> 00:50:10.140 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:50:10.140 --> 00:50:11.370 align:middle line:90%
You guys stay here.

00:50:11.370 --> 00:50:12.720 align:middle line:90%
I'll be back with the baby.

00:50:12.720 --> 00:50:15.690 align:middle line:84%
So while I was trying
to escape labor,

00:50:15.690 --> 00:50:18.555 align:middle line:84%
I met a place that I think a
lot of women meet in labor.

00:50:18.555 --> 00:50:21.790 align:middle line:90%


00:50:21.790 --> 00:50:22.975 align:middle line:90%
The rock and the hard place.

00:50:22.975 --> 00:50:25.865 align:middle line:90%


00:50:25.865 --> 00:50:26.665 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:50:26.665 --> 00:50:30.000 align:middle line:90%


00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:32.760 align:middle line:84%
Every single woman who
is having natural birth

00:50:32.760 --> 00:50:34.683 align:middle line:84%
feels like that at
a certain point.

00:50:34.683 --> 00:50:37.650 align:middle line:90%


00:50:37.650 --> 00:50:41.550 align:middle line:84%
The rock is I'm not pushing
because it hurts too much.

00:50:41.550 --> 00:50:44.120 align:middle line:90%


00:50:44.120 --> 00:50:46.790 align:middle line:90%
And the hard place is OK, then.

00:50:46.790 --> 00:50:48.380 align:middle line:90%
You're staying pregnant forever.

00:50:48.380 --> 00:50:51.170 align:middle line:90%
And it's going to hurt forever.

00:50:51.170 --> 00:50:54.512 align:middle line:84%
So it's the most
infuriating place to be.

00:50:54.512 --> 00:50:57.320 align:middle line:90%
That pain is just awful.

00:50:57.320 --> 00:50:59.870 align:middle line:84%
In the process, I told
everybody around me

00:50:59.870 --> 00:51:01.160 align:middle line:90%
that they weren't helping me.

00:51:01.160 --> 00:51:02.094 align:middle line:90%
Don't move.

00:51:02.094 --> 00:51:02.900 align:middle line:90%
Ow.

00:51:02.900 --> 00:51:05.150 align:middle line:84%
That I wanted them to get
out and get my mother, who I

00:51:05.150 --> 00:51:07.125 align:middle line:90%
didn't even want at the birth.

00:51:07.125 --> 00:51:08.750 align:middle line:84%
I told everyone,
you're not helping me.

00:51:08.750 --> 00:51:10.620 align:middle line:90%
Get out.

00:51:10.620 --> 00:51:11.420 align:middle line:90%
That was just me.

00:51:11.420 --> 00:51:14.450 align:middle line:90%
Everybody doesn't say that.

00:51:14.450 --> 00:51:17.280 align:middle line:84%
And I sat in the bathtub and
looked at the faucet and said,

00:51:17.280 --> 00:51:18.080 align:middle line:90%
it's me.

00:51:18.080 --> 00:51:23.030 align:middle line:84%
I'm either dying or I'm
pushing the baby out.

00:51:23.030 --> 00:51:24.890 align:middle line:84%
The fact that I had
a difficult labor--

00:51:24.890 --> 00:51:26.834 align:middle line:90%
I'm ready to do it.

00:51:26.834 --> 00:51:29.750 align:middle line:90%
I'm ready to push.

00:51:29.750 --> 00:51:31.640 align:middle line:84%
It's a good thing
for me as a midwife,

00:51:31.640 --> 00:51:34.550 align:middle line:84%
because I feel that
I know how hard it

00:51:34.550 --> 00:51:37.930 align:middle line:84%
can get for a woman who's
going through labor.

00:51:37.930 --> 00:51:40.690 align:middle line:84%
And when I went back to
work, the first woman

00:51:40.690 --> 00:51:43.570 align:middle line:84%
I looked at in labor,
I was of no help to.

00:51:43.570 --> 00:51:46.370 align:middle line:84%
I just looked at her
and I said, I know.

00:51:46.370 --> 00:51:47.170 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:51:47.170 --> 00:51:49.930 align:middle line:84%
And I was lost in the
empathy, because I

00:51:49.930 --> 00:51:53.120 align:middle line:84%
felt so sorry that she was on
the other side of that place.

00:51:53.120 --> 00:51:55.435 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't-- and
that she had to be there.

00:51:55.435 --> 00:52:04.090 align:middle line:90%


00:52:04.090 --> 00:52:04.930 align:middle line:90%
No, no.

00:52:04.930 --> 00:52:05.730 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:52:05.730 --> 00:52:33.050 align:middle line:90%


00:52:33.050 --> 00:52:34.408 align:middle line:90%
>> 10:12.

00:52:34.408 --> 00:52:44.818 align:middle line:90%


00:52:44.818 --> 00:52:46.360 align:middle line:84%
>> I can never hear
anything on this.

00:52:46.360 --> 00:52:47.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Try like this.

00:52:47.890 --> 00:52:48.850 align:middle line:90%
Close your eyes.

00:52:48.850 --> 00:52:51.340 align:middle line:84%
>> The whole insurance
thing has been crazy.

00:52:51.340 --> 00:52:53.650 align:middle line:84%
I called and I
said, I'm pregnant.

00:52:53.650 --> 00:52:54.940 align:middle line:90%
OK, who's your doctor?

00:52:54.940 --> 00:52:56.680 align:middle line:90%
Well, I don't have a doctor.

00:52:56.680 --> 00:52:58.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm going with a midwife.

00:52:58.120 --> 00:53:00.790 align:middle line:84%
And they were like,
OK, but which hospital?

00:53:00.790 --> 00:53:02.800 align:middle line:84%
Everyone I talked to
there was just like,

00:53:02.800 --> 00:53:03.640 align:middle line:90%
what do you mean a home birth?

00:53:03.640 --> 00:53:05.807 align:middle line:84%
But aren't you going to
have a doctor delivering it?

00:53:05.807 --> 00:53:06.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, no.

00:53:06.610 --> 00:53:07.652 align:middle line:90%
Why is this so difficult?

00:53:07.652 --> 00:53:10.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't understand why this
is such a difficult thing.

00:53:10.330 --> 00:53:12.820 align:middle line:84%
Everybody was acting like I
had a third eye or something.

00:53:12.820 --> 00:53:14.652 align:middle line:90%
>> Officially, 37 weeks.

00:53:14.652 --> 00:53:16.360 align:middle line:84%
>> We'll do the beta
strep culture today.

00:53:16.360 --> 00:53:19.030 align:middle line:84%
>> What I really had a hard
time understanding is that

00:53:19.030 --> 00:53:22.090 align:middle line:84%
it's cheaper to have
a birth with midwives.

00:53:22.090 --> 00:53:24.560 align:middle line:84%
You'd think they
would be all over it.

00:53:24.560 --> 00:53:26.950 align:middle line:84%
>> There's some hospitals in
New Hampshire where a normal

00:53:26.950 --> 00:53:31.130 align:middle line:84%
spontaneous vaginal
delivery is around $13,000.

00:53:31.130 --> 00:53:31.930 align:middle line:10%
Hello.

00:53:31.930 --> 00:53:34.450 align:middle line:10%
I'm charging $4,000
for everything.

00:53:34.450 --> 00:53:37.400 align:middle line:84%
That includes the
post-natal care, everything,

00:53:37.400 --> 00:53:38.770 align:middle line:90%
including the facility fee.

00:53:38.770 --> 00:53:43.300 align:middle line:84%
>> So it makes you wonder
what their agenda is.

00:53:43.300 --> 00:53:49.540 align:middle line:84%
>> The insurance companies
are part of the establishment.

00:53:49.540 --> 00:53:52.630 align:middle line:84%
And so when the
obstetricians who

00:53:52.630 --> 00:53:55.360 align:middle line:84%
are giving the advice to
the insurance companies

00:53:55.360 --> 00:53:58.900 align:middle line:84%
say that home birth is dangerous
or that midwives are not

00:53:58.900 --> 00:54:02.020 align:middle line:84%
as safe as doctors and
all of this nonsense,

00:54:02.020 --> 00:54:06.280 align:middle line:84%
the establishment CEO in
the insurance companies

00:54:06.280 --> 00:54:07.447 align:middle line:90%
believes them.

00:54:07.447 --> 00:54:09.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I've interviewed a
lot of nurse midwives.

00:54:09.280 --> 00:54:11.470 align:middle line:84%
And I noticed that as soon
as their practice reaches

00:54:11.470 --> 00:54:14.242 align:middle line:84%
more than 30% of the women
in a certain hospital,

00:54:14.242 --> 00:54:15.700 align:middle line:84%
the doctors will
start firing them,

00:54:15.700 --> 00:54:18.560 align:middle line:84%
because that's too
much competition.

00:54:18.560 --> 00:54:21.800 align:middle line:84%
>> The AMA, as the trade
organization for physicians,

00:54:21.800 --> 00:54:24.860 align:middle line:84%
has a very clear,
publicly-stated stance that

00:54:24.860 --> 00:54:29.690 align:middle line:84%
they will not support anything
that allows for non-physicians

00:54:29.690 --> 00:54:32.290 align:middle line:84%
to do anything
that physicians do.

00:54:32.290 --> 00:54:34.280 align:middle line:10%
You want to talk big
lobby, big dollars,

00:54:34.280 --> 00:54:37.050 align:middle line:10%
they can call a lot of shots.

00:54:37.050 --> 00:54:39.830 align:middle line:84%
>> I have made several attempts
to get this claim reprocessed.

00:54:39.830 --> 00:54:42.440 align:middle line:84%
When I explained to them
that we were clearly covered,

00:54:42.440 --> 00:54:44.810 align:middle line:84%
she agreed that the claim
needed to be reprocessed.

00:54:44.810 --> 00:54:46.970 align:middle line:84%
But of course, the
computers were down.

00:54:46.970 --> 00:54:50.340 align:middle line:84%
>> This is what we go
through, all to get paid.

00:54:50.340 --> 00:54:51.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, Millie.

00:54:51.140 --> 00:54:51.973 align:middle line:90%
Is Marcia available?

00:54:51.973 --> 00:54:54.140 align:middle line:84%
>> When I called the heads
of the insurance company,

00:54:54.140 --> 00:54:55.560 align:middle line:90%
I met with them face to face.

00:54:55.560 --> 00:54:57.860 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh,
our hands are tied.

00:54:57.860 --> 00:54:58.890 align:middle line:90%
I said, no, they're not.

00:54:58.890 --> 00:54:59.690 align:middle line:90%
They're not.

00:54:59.690 --> 00:55:01.080 align:middle line:90%
You just don't care.

00:55:01.080 --> 00:55:02.340 align:middle line:90%
It's not about health care.

00:55:02.340 --> 00:55:04.490 align:middle line:84%
It's not about saving
money for consumers.

00:55:04.490 --> 00:55:06.800 align:middle line:84%
And it's not about women
and babies, that's for sure.

00:55:06.800 --> 00:55:08.480 align:middle line:90%
>> We got the authorization.

00:55:08.480 --> 00:55:11.300 align:middle line:84%
Claims department is not
reading the claim correctly.

00:55:11.300 --> 00:55:13.100 align:middle line:84%
It's like I'm begging
you to get paid.

00:55:13.100 --> 00:55:14.900 align:middle line:84%
Your members did
not have to beg us

00:55:14.900 --> 00:55:16.610 align:middle line:90%
to come in and get treatment.

00:55:16.610 --> 00:55:18.693 align:middle line:84%
You'll try and
find her tomorrow.

00:55:18.693 --> 00:55:20.360 align:middle line:84%
>> We talk about
giving mothers options.

00:55:20.360 --> 00:55:22.730 align:middle line:84%
What isn't talked
about is the degree

00:55:22.730 --> 00:55:25.730 align:middle line:84%
to which options are being
closed off to mothers.

00:55:25.730 --> 00:55:28.490 align:middle line:10%
One example is birth
centers, which at this point

00:55:28.490 --> 00:55:30.380 align:middle line:10%
is at almost an all-time low.

00:55:30.380 --> 00:55:39.660 align:middle line:90%


00:55:39.660 --> 00:55:43.290 align:middle line:84%
>> My decision to not renew
my malpractice came from a lot

00:55:43.290 --> 00:55:44.140 align:middle line:90%
of different places.

00:55:44.140 --> 00:55:45.450 align:middle line:84%
Number one, we were
getting letters

00:55:45.450 --> 00:55:47.070 align:middle line:84%
from our insurance companies
saying that they're

00:55:47.070 --> 00:55:48.360 align:middle line:90%
going to increase the rates.

00:55:48.360 --> 00:55:50.340 align:middle line:84%
We aren't making
a living anymore.

00:55:50.340 --> 00:55:53.100 align:middle line:84%
>> A lot of people say, oh,
it's an economic battle.

00:55:53.100 --> 00:55:54.690 align:middle line:84%
Of course it's an
economic battle.

00:55:54.690 --> 00:55:58.170 align:middle line:90%
It's a billion-dollar industry.

00:55:58.170 --> 00:56:02.640 align:middle line:84%
>> We spend twice as much in
this country per birth than any

00:56:02.640 --> 00:56:04.180 align:middle line:90%
other country in the world.

00:56:04.180 --> 00:56:07.380 align:middle line:84%
This is one of those
very rare instances

00:56:07.380 --> 00:56:09.355 align:middle line:90%
where cheaper is truly better.

00:56:09.355 --> 00:56:10.980 align:middle line:84%
>> It works in all
the other countries.

00:56:10.980 --> 00:56:14.010 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at our data,
the amount of money we spend

00:56:14.010 --> 00:56:16.920 align:middle line:84%
versus the outcomes
we get, it sucks.

00:56:16.920 --> 00:56:19.860 align:middle line:84%
There are countries that spend
a third of what we have and have

00:56:19.860 --> 00:56:21.550 align:middle line:90%
lower infant mortality.

00:56:21.550 --> 00:56:24.460 align:middle line:84%
So more doesn't mean
more in this case.

00:56:24.460 --> 00:56:26.327 align:middle line:90%
And maybe less is more.

00:56:26.327 --> 00:56:28.662 align:middle line:90%
>> Run.

00:56:28.662 --> 00:56:30.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are you running so fast?

00:56:30.530 --> 00:56:32.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Because she's
sitting in the car.

00:56:32.070 --> 00:56:36.960 align:middle line:90%


00:56:36.960 --> 00:56:38.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Sorry to make a
pregnant woman run.

00:56:38.850 --> 00:56:40.910 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:56:40.910 --> 00:56:41.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Stopping was painful.

00:56:41.930 --> 00:56:45.860 align:middle line:90%


00:56:45.860 --> 00:56:48.510 align:middle line:84%
Abby, this feels a little
bit like living on the edge,

00:56:48.510 --> 00:56:49.310 align:middle line:90%
in a way.

00:56:49.310 --> 00:56:51.740 align:middle line:84%
But to tell you
the truth, there's

00:56:51.740 --> 00:56:53.330 align:middle line:90%
a lot worse edges to live on.

00:56:53.330 --> 00:56:55.910 align:middle line:84%
And when you've been there,
this doesn't feel that scary.

00:56:55.910 --> 00:57:18.170 align:middle line:90%


00:57:18.170 --> 00:57:21.350 align:middle line:84%
>> She has some
over here for that.

00:57:21.350 --> 00:57:25.490 align:middle line:84%
>> If I am lecturing to a
roomful of obstetricians and I

00:57:25.490 --> 00:57:28.160 align:middle line:84%
put the word home and the word
birth together in the same

00:57:28.160 --> 00:57:31.950 align:middle line:84%
sentence, there's just
hysteria in the room.

00:57:31.950 --> 00:57:35.030 align:middle line:84%
And then what I always
do is say, OK, OK.

00:57:35.030 --> 00:57:38.570 align:middle line:84%
I want everyone in this room
who has ever attended a home

00:57:38.570 --> 00:57:40.850 align:middle line:90%
birth, raise your hand.

00:57:40.850 --> 00:57:41.980 align:middle line:90%
Nobody.

00:57:41.980 --> 00:57:44.680 align:middle line:90%
They've never seen a home birth.

00:57:44.680 --> 00:57:48.310 align:middle line:84%
So then I say, you're all
like the geographers who

00:57:48.310 --> 00:57:52.420 align:middle line:84%
are trying to describe a
country they've never been to,

00:57:52.420 --> 00:57:55.135 align:middle line:84%
because they're too
afraid to go there.

00:57:55.135 --> 00:57:56.125 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:57:56.125 --> 00:58:04.810 align:middle line:90%


00:58:04.810 --> 00:58:07.570 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:58:07.570 --> 00:58:08.500 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:58:08.500 --> 00:58:09.790 align:middle line:90%
No, it hurts so much.

00:58:09.790 --> 00:58:22.300 align:middle line:90%


00:58:22.300 --> 00:58:23.100 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:58:23.100 --> 00:58:27.150 align:middle line:90%


00:58:27.150 --> 00:58:28.257 align:middle line:90%
>> Sorry.

00:58:28.257 --> 00:58:32.550 align:middle line:90%


00:58:32.550 --> 00:58:33.598 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:58:33.598 --> 00:58:43.245 align:middle line:90%


00:58:43.245 --> 00:58:44.045 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:58:44.045 --> 00:58:51.870 align:middle line:90%


00:58:51.870 --> 00:58:54.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes, mama.

